    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Book demos with Google Calendar and Gmail at scale\n\n**Pattern:** Meeting Scheduling · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nBook demos with Google Calendar and Gmail at scale. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual booking is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Booking Form Submission → Normalize Booking Payload → Check Calendar Availability → Slot Free? → Create Calendar Event → Send Confirmation (Gmail) → Hold Until Reminder Time → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to meeting scheduling without manual effort\n- Anyone automating booking in healthcare\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "8e97d1ef-ce5b-56c8-0aa3-83d85782bcb2",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "40e12ca5-ba1c-becc-6063-3b17a63c22b1",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
